<title>BUGbot Wheels Module - Open source hardware on wheels!</title>
<description>
<![CDATA[<p><img src="http://blog.makezine.com/bugbot_by_ilan.jpg" height="375" width="500" border="0" hspace="4" vspace="4" alt="Bugbot By Ilan" /><br />
<embed src="http://blip.tv/play/gd4T36k2kI0m" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="500" height="375" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed> <br />
<a href="http://community.buglabs.net/agibb/posts/36-BUGbot-Wheels-Module-by-Ilan-Moyer">BUGbot Wheels Module by Ilan Moyer</a>-</p>

<blockquote>Ilan Moyer stopped by the Test Kitchen for a visit.  With the <a href="http://bugcommunity.com/wiki/index.php/BUGbase">CAD files</a> he downloaded from BUG he was able to fabricate a base for wheels.  The wheels use DC motors and a motor driver.  They are programmable over serial, but we were trying to get the data through the Samtec connector that day. A truely awesome invention!</blockquote>
 
